  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nAs of 5.0.35, imports from node packages now throw compilation errors. This may or may not be intended behaviour, but it is a breaking change from 5.0.34 compiler - which seems to work just fine. I much prefer to have these imports over relative or absolute paths to the node modules\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nImport a file from OpenZeppelin using `import { ERC20Mintable } from \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20Mintable.sol\"`, inherit and implement the constructor in a basic ERC20 token and try to compile the contract\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nOne would expect the contract to compile just fine and utilise the imported library\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\nParserError: Source \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20Mintable.sol\" not found: File import callback not supported\r\nimport { ERC20Mintable } from \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20Mintable.sol\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Pop_OS (Ubuntu 19.04)\r\n* Ethereum client: `ganache-cli 6.7`\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.35\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 10.15\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.8.0\r\n",
